2. 樂曲改編及演奏家 Performers & Arrangers




厝Home- composed by James Chen

 以下的"厝"乃是一個試聽版，在旋律上又加了人聲的部份。CD所收錄的僅有單簧管與鋼琴，但在譜寫這首曲子時是有歌詞的概念的，因此在放上這版本讓您欣賞，或按上方的播放器純粹欣賞音樂版本。 

This version of "Home" is a demo with a voice singing along with the melody line. What we have in the CD is simply clarinet and piano, however, the song was composed with some lyrics in mind. Please enjoy the CD version by clicking the mp3 player above or the voice demo below.

  
Home from This Is My Father's World
  
 
 
陳建銘James Chen

　　美國科羅拉多大學「音樂藝術博士」（Doctor of Musical Arts），主修「單簧管演奏與教學」。1998年於淡水工商管理學院（真理大學）任專任助理教授暨音樂系籌備處主任乙職，2000-2004年擔任真理大學音樂應用學系主任。現為真理大學音樂應用學系專任助理教授。
　　歷年來於臺北、中壢、臺中、臺南及 美國拉斯維加斯、洛杉磯等地舉辦單簧管獨奏、室內樂音樂會；曾擔任管弦樂團之副指揮暨管樂指導，隨樂團於台灣各地、美國林肯中心及日本演出；並擔任大學術科考試、全國音樂比賽、及各地音樂班評審；暨應邀於各校或各地演講演出。目前擔任心音室內樂團團長。　　著有「如何開始學豎笛」，譯有「歷史上的單簧管名家」，編曲與出版CD「與我同行」及「這是天父世界」；並有文章及專文於雜誌或報紙刊登。

莊憶芬Ifen Chuang
　　　美國克裡夫蘭音樂學院（The Cleveland Institute of Music）鋼琴演奏碩士。　　五歲開始習琴，啟蒙於父親莊松輝牧師，十歲即擔任教會詩班之伴奏，在無任何樂理的基礎下，卻能將每首曲子配上豐富的和弦。高中畢業後隨即赴美就讀於克裡夫蘭音樂學院。　　在美期間主修鋼琴，但在雙鋼琴及伴奏方面皆有深度的學習，在視奏的能力更獲得學校教授的讚賞。曾應邀至Altoona、Lima、Hudson、Ashland、Chicago等地區舉行鋼琴獨奏會，當地的報上記載：「是有天賦及具有震憾力之鋼琴家」、「對音樂的表達熱情澎湃，她具有舞臺的魅力」…等等。　　回台後大小演出不斷，足跡踏遍台灣北中南、離島地區，及美國拉斯維加斯與洛杉磯等地，除鋼琴獨奏外，並舉辦過雙鋼琴及與各樣樂器的室內樂音樂會；同時並擔任大學聯招評審會之委員。目前任教於真理大學、關渡基督書院及淡江中學。
    Miss Ifen Chuang graduated from the Cleveland Institute of Music in 1997, receiving her Master degree in Piano Performance.    Miss Chuang began her piano lesson from her father when she was five years old, and started accompanying the church choir at the age of ten. Ifen can accompany any piece with rich variety of harmony without any tutor. She went to the States as soon as she graduated from the Senior High School.    Ifen had splendid ability in piano performance and accompanying. She gained lots of recognition from the professors. The news gave her tremendous applause when she was invited to perform in Altoona, Lima, Hudson, Ashland and Chicago.   After coming back to Taiwan, Ifen holds recitals and concerts, gets invited being the jury for numorous competitions. She now teaches at Aletheia University, Christ’s College and Tam-Kang High School.
 
 
 
 
      Dr. Chien-Ming Chen, received his DMA in University of Colorado at Boulder, USA in 1997. Being a clarinetist, he has been performing as a soloist or with the orchestra throughout Taiwan, Japan and the States.     Mr. Chen was the Dean of the department of Applied music, Aletheia University, Taipei, 2000-2004. His Writing includes a book, “How to Start Playing Your Clarinet” (both in Chinese and English), a Chinese translation of ”Clarinet Virtuosi of the Past”. Joining ”Walking along with Me”, ”This Is My Father’s World” is his second CD.



心音室內樂團Singing Music: https://sites.google.com/site/singingchambermusic/        ＊  E-mail:  clarinettogo@gmail.com, Mobile: 886-956-560910
